		(descr "Motor phase solder pad, 4x4mm SMD + 5 stitching vias. Phase A/B/C output (HS-source/LS-drain switching node). 100A/sqrt3=58A RMS burst per phase; 16mm2 pad + 5 vias spreading to B.Cu/inner phase copper -> ~150A per IPC-2152 (~2.5x margin). Phase 4-v3 Sai-locked option (b) 2026-05-25. Vias carry the MOTOR phase net (NOT +VMOTOR); VMOTOR plane is isolated by zone antipad.")
